HQ is one of the biggest electric companies in North America. Its mission is to generate and deliver service throughout Canadian province of Québec. For this purpose it has to manage a large call center: nearly 500 agents handling 26 different call types. For our study, daily arrival counts related to four call types were gathered over a 6-month period (May–November 2010). Call arrival process shows different behavior for Mondays and Fridays from the three other working weekdays. Thus, to study the arrival under typical repeating pattern we focus solely on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays. Over this selected period of 76 days the call type 1 (




